{"metadata":{"role":"symbol","roleHeading":"Structure","modules":[{"name":"ReadiumShared"}],"title":"DOMRange","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"DOMRange"}],"externalID":"s:13ReadiumShared8DOMRangeV","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"DOMRange"}],"symbolKind":"struct"},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/ReadiumShared\/DOMRange"},"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"kind":"symbol","topicSections":[{"anchor":"Structures","generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/ReadiumShared\/DOMRange\/Point"],"title":"Structures"},{"anchor":"Initializers","generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/ReadiumShared\/DOMRange\/init(json:warnings:)","doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/ReadiumShared\/DOMRange\/init(start:end:)"],"title":"Initializers"},{"anchor":"Instance-Properties","generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/ReadiumShared\/DOMRange\/json"],"title":"Instance Properties"},{"anchor":"Default-Implementations","generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/ReadiumShared\/DOMRange\/CustomDebugStringConvertible-Implementations","doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/ReadiumShared\/DOMRange\/Equatable-Implementations"],"title":"Default Implementations"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/ReadiumShared"]]},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"This construct enables a serializable representation of a DOM Range."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["iOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"DOMRange"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"anchor":"overview","level":2,"text":"Overview","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In a DOM Range object, the startContainer + startOffset tuple represents the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"start"},{"type":"text","text":" boundary"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"point. Similarly, the the endContainer + endOffset tuple represents the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"end"},{"type":"text","text":" boundary point."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"In both cases, the start\/endContainer property is a pointer to either a DOM text node, or a DOM"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"element (this typically depends on the mechanism from which the DOM Range instance originates,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"for example when obtaining the currently-selected document fragment using the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"window.selection"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"API). In the case of a DOM text node, the start\/endOffset corresponds to a position within the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"character data. In the case of a DOM element node, the start\/endOffset corresponds to a position"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that designates a child text node."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Note that ","type":"text"},{"code":"end","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" field is optional. When only the start field is specified, the domRange object","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"represents a “collapsed” range that has identical ","type":"text"},{"code":"start","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"code":"end","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" boundary points.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"https:\/\/github.com\/readium\/architecture\/blob\/master\/models\/locators\/extensions\/html.md#the-domrange-object","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"relationshipsSections":[{"type":"conformsTo","identifiers":["doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/ReadiumShared\/JSONEquatable","doc:\/\/Readium\/s28CustomDebugStringConvertibleP","doc:\/\/Readium